  <front>
   <head>SONNET. TO MR. J. PAICE.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">JOSEPH, the worthy Son of worthy Sire,</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Who well repay'st thy pious parents care</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To train thee in the ways of Virtue fair,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And early with the love of Truth inspire.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">What farther can my closing eyes desire</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To see, but that by wedlock thou repair</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">The waste of death; and raise a virtuous heir</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">To build our House, e'er I in peace retire?</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="pentameter">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Youth is the time for Love: Then choose a Wife,</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">With prudence choose; 'tis Nature's genuine voice;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">And what she truly dictates must be good;</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Neglected once that prime, our remnant life</l>
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Is sour'd, or sadden'd, by an ill-tim'd choice,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="10">Or lonely, dull, and friendless solitude.</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
